text: I like how Dungeon Synth is a music genre specifically created for and by autists. Zero pretense, no one would ever argue otherwise. With other esoteric electronic music genres people at least pretend to dance to it and stuff, but not here. Also Varg Vikernes sort of invented it?

It's music made for a 32 year old guy to play some video game to in a basement while drinking beer in his underwear at 3 AM. They even put the word "dungeon" in the name. You just know what you're getting, no pretense. Not my thing personally per se but I still deeply respect it.

I feel like people watching streamers like Tyler1 or youtubers while eating is a natural instinct to alleviate this (and actually quite successfully), you hear people talk about how it's good to have no distractions when eating and focus on the food, but no one does it for long.

Apparently when I was a baby I hated eating so my grandpa came up with a trick where he stood on the opposite side of a window and put clothespins on his nose and ears like a DIY clown and did funny dances to distract me while I ate. Food goes down better when you're having fun.

One type of old school book you often notice at secondhand bookstores, but also never see anyone discuss or mention online is books about various ship disasters or airplane crashes titled like: "The 21 Worst Shipwrecks of All Time" or "History of Train Derailments". Very quaint.
Have you read them all? Admirable feat in its own right

The first Tolstoy (Pyotr Andreyevich Tolstoy) was a torturer and headhunter who earned his title by tracking down the Russian prince in Italy and tricking him into coming back where he tortured and murdered him by order of the king. Was seen as unscrupulous, a hated traitor, etc.

The English Wikipedia page mentions that Tolstoy "was by nature eminently fitted" for the post he was appointed for afterwards as "the head of the Secret Chancellery, or official torture chamber". I don't think you need too many textbooks on physiognomy for this one.

"Human Resources" management is a New Age-y fad similar to "business hypnosis" or those guys who read affirmations about being a successful CEO every morning before going to their regular job. The entire practice should be restricted to a few Scientologist organizations at most.
Having a Human Resources department is like having a dedicated Transcendental Meditation office room or keeping a resident Human Design expert.

Not to disrespect his role in it, but it's easy to see that most easily solvable and more mediocre elements of Twin Peaks seem to originate with Mark Frost and the deeper enigmas everyone is obsessed with still trying to solve are part of David Lynch's personal vision for it.

Mark Frost: What if nukes were demonic and nuclear bombs opened portal for demons to enter? Psst, kid, they won't tell you this, but the US government hired some Nazis after WW2...
